Is a Polish champion road racing cyclist, currently riding for UCI Professional Continental team Ceramica Flaminia, having ridden for them since 2006. He is ranked 64th in the CyclingRanking.com national overall (1869–2008) ranking.[2]He started as a trainee for the Krakus Swoszowice team, staying with them from 1998–2002, and then riding for Pacyfik Torun from 2003–2005. In 2006 he began a professional career with the Italian team Ceramica Flaminia-Bossini Docce. In 2007, he won the Polish national road race championship.[3]

Was a teenage star of the 1973 In Desert and Wilderness movie and miniseries (1974), where he played Stas Tarkowski, having Monika Rosca as young partner. He is the son of Stefania Medrzak.He later did acting studies and has played a few movie roles. But he has always been focused rather on theatre. As of June 2004, he has been a director and actor of the Ochota theater in Warsaw. He didn't really want to play Stas. He went to the auditions because he was interested in technical aspects of cinematography. Some time after being chosen, he wanted to decline, but the wife of the movie's director persuaded him to stay.

Is a Polish sprint canoer. Mendelski has represented Poland in both the K-1 200 m and 500 m, but specialises in the former discipline, the shortest race-distance. At the world championships he finished sixth (2001), fourth (2002) and sixth (2003) before finally making the podium at the 2005 worlds in Zagreb, Croatia, where he won the silver medal.Mendelski also won two silver medals in the K-4 1000 m event at the ICF Canoe Sprint World Championships, earning them in 2006 and 2007, and a bronze in the K-4 500 m event at 2006.

Is a Polish historian, leftist politician, former vice-Speaker of the Sejm and a former member of the Socjaldemokracja Polska party (Polish Social-Democracy).In the past he used to be member of the communist Polish United Workers' Party (PZPR) (1970–1990) and later its social-democratic successor, Socjaldemokracja Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej (Social Democracy of the Republic of Poland). In the years 1993-2004 he was a prominent member of Unia Pracy (Labour Union). He left the Labour Union after Socjaldemokracja Polska (Social Democracy of Poland) was founded by Marek Borowski.

Is a Polish ski jumper who has competed since 2001. He finished 6th in the team large hill and 40th in the individual normal hill events at the 2002 Winter Olympics in Salt Lake City.At the 2003 FIS Nordic World Ski Championships in Val di Fiemme, Pochwala finished 39th in the individual normal hill event. He finished 31st in the individual event of the 2002 Ski-flying World Championships in Harrachov.

Poet, author of songs, publicist, menedzer and animator of culture.He has been an artist since his youth, especially an author of poetic texts and songs, as well as essays. He debuted his work during his studies in 1991 in the "Mloda Polska" magazine.

The son of an Olympic athlete father and artist mother who together encouraged a love of art and the classics.[2] During his childhood Rut was introduced to the Pompeiien Frescos as well as Renaissance and Baroque art, which have influenced his oils on canvas, murals, and graphic works. Rut had his first showing in Warsaw at the age of eleven. [3]Trained in Art Conservation at the Academy of Fine Arts in Warsaw, Rut continued his education in New York City at the Pratt Institute in Brooklyn and at Columbia University in Manhattan. He eventually took a job in art conservation for the Biltmore House in Asheville, North Carolina, traveling the east coast restoring large scale murals in museums and mansions for such clients as the Smithsonian Institution and the U.S. Treasury Department in Washington, DC, the New Jersey State House in Trenton, the Gusman Center for the Arts and Vizcaya Museum in Miami. [4]

A Polish striker who plays for Helsingin Jalkapalloklubi in the Finnish Veikkausliiga. He also has a German citizenship.a Polish striker who plays for Helsingin Jalkapalloklubi in the Finnish Veikkausliiga. He also has a German citizenship.He joined Veikkausliiga side HJK on April 16, 2008 on a Bosman. [1] He made his debut on April 28, 2008 against IFK Mariehamn and scored his first goal for the club. His first hat-trick for HJK came on May 19, 2008 against Tampere United in a 5-1 home victory.[2] After his successful start for the club he suffered an injury and couldn't take his place back in the team. In the end of August, HJK announced that he is free to find a new club.

Polish footballer currently playing midfield for Ruch Chorzów.He began his career with MOSiR Pruszcz Gdanski (fall 1990) upon completing high school. He began playing at MOSiR Pruszcz Gdanski in 1980 as a youth. He then moved on to Lyn Sepopol (1991). In 1992 he transferred to Stomil Olsztyn and helped them advance to the Ekstraklasa in 1994.

A Polish footballer. He began his career playing from youth level as a striker in Zaglebie Sosnowiec (debuted in June 2001)and was top-scorer for his club by helping them get promoted twice the years Stolpa was there. His appearances attracted Tromsø I.L. in Norway and this was he first transfer. After a short loan pass in Belgium club V.C. Eendracht Aalst 2002 he returned back to Tromsø I.L. participated in Royal League and played with them in UEFA cup stages.In 2006 he was playing for Enköpings SK in Sweden and help them get promoted in Superettan.From December 2006, he signed a two-year-contract with Allsvenskan club Gefle IF.

The Polish architect, designer of artistic glass in architecture. He finished studies at the Architecture Department of University of Technology in Wroclaw (1978-85). He took glass-window studies at the Fine AQrt Academy at UMK in Torun (1982-85). He worked as an assistant in the Painting and Sculpture Establishment at the Architecture Dept. of Wroclaw's Institute. In 1987 together with his wife, architect Beata Urbanowicz, he established his own studio Archiglass in Wroclaw.
